title: For Sale:  Ruger SR40
postcontent:
I’m the first owner on this Ruger SR40, it was purchased new from Cabelas in Hamburg. I’m interested in selling it to fund another gun purchase. 

These SR series of pistols from Ruger are probably the most underappreciated semi autos around. During my time with this SR40 I’ve experienced zero issues, and find it a pleasure to shoot. If you do some research, you’ll find that a common opinion on these is that they are a very soft shooting .40.  The fully adjustable sights get back on target quickly, while the short reset allows for fast & acccurate follow up shots.

This gun is fun to shoot, and is a fantastic all purpose pistol. It’s suitable for range fun, home defense, and concealed carry. The SR grip and slide are slim for a full sized pistol, and you can really feel that when carrying. The accessory rail will accommodate a tactical light or laser for home defense or tactical training purposes. The .40 S&W is often considered snappy, and ballistically nothing to sneeze at, however the SR’s high bore axis grip keeps it comfortable for a day of shooting.

The weapon has been meticulously maintained, and has been upgraded with a stainless steel guide rod, and new recoil spring purchased from Galloway Precision.  The factory polymer rod and spring are in good condition, and are included with the pistol.

Included in the sale are:	Original Ruger pistol case and literature
				        Two 15 round Magazines. 
				         One magazine Loader

title: For Trade:  M&M M10 AK-47
postcontent:
I recently got this AK in a trade. It's a great gun, but I'd rather something in 5.56 or 5.45. Actually, I will happily keep this rifle, but I promised my wife I wouldn't buy any more guns this year... so trading is where it's at.

The M10 is a new manufacture Romanian rifle imported and converted by M&M industries. Unlike a WASR, the M10 isn't cobbled together from parts kits. This means much greater reliability and impressive accuracy.

Here are some reviews:
http://www.survivalblog.com/2012/06/pats-product-review-mm-m10-762-rifle.html
http://thefiringline.com/forums/showthread.php?t=493513
http://www.thetruthaboutguns.com/2013/10/joe-grine/gun-review-mm-m10-762-rifle/

I will add pictures when I get home from work.

I do want to mention that, like many AKs, the finish on this gun is kinda rough. It doesn't impact function, but it will not win beauty contests. This rifle is a definite candidate for duracote.

I will include the original polymer magazine, a one-point sling it came with from the original owner, and (for the right trade) 4 East German AK mags with their case.

Looking for trades, but if you want to make a cash offer, I'll consider it.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Kg-9
postcontent:
Item Description: Interdymic kg9 with factory 36 round mag brief history on it 

Interdynamic of America, Inc was a distributor in business in Miami from 1981 to 1984.

They offered the KG-9, the KG-99, and the KG-99M "mini pistol".
The KG-9 was an open bolt "paramilitary" blued steel pistol, sales of which the BATF stopped due to the open bolt being too easy to convert to full- auto.

The KG-99 was the same gun only firing from a closed bolt.
It had a 36 round magazine, a 5 inch vented shroud barrel and was made of stainless steel.

Monday, March 3, 2014 

Honey Toast Cafe, 12520 SW Farmington Road, Beaverton, OR 97005

This class is open all residents of Oregon, Washington, Idaho, Nevada and California. This course exceeds all firearms safety training requirements of Oregon's concealed handgun law pursuant to ORS 166.291(f)(G). You will receive a certificate of completion which you can submit to your local Sheriff's office with your concealed handgun license application. 

Subjects covered are: Basic Handgun Safety, Tactical Issues, CCW Firearms, Ammunition, Holsters, Gun Free Zones, Reciprocity, Storage, Oregon "Use of deadly force laws" 

After attending this class you will have a fundamental understanding about firearm and handgun safety and the rights and responsibilities associated with the carrying of a concealed Handgun in the State of Oregon. 

This is NOT a live firing class. Do NOT bring a firearm with you to the class.

postcontent: Honest sellers should know to temporarily deactivate a listing once a deal has been arranged. Allowing a listing to remain activated shows greed, disrespect, and dishonesty. If a seller makes an arrangement with the buyer on Friday to meet on Sunday, don't sell the item to someone else on Saturday! In other words, don't be a greedy asshole! Armslist doesn't have a system in place yet to check buyers and sellers feedback but that don't mean buyers and sellers don't keep records of their own. Taurus PT92 In 1980, we purchased the Beretta factory in Sao Paulo, Brazil "lock, stock and barrel" and immediately sought to improve on the Beretta design, resulting in the popular and acclaimed Taurus 92. Always looking to raise the bar, we've taken this year's models a step further than they've ever been. Most notable is Taurus' specially designed drop hammer forged ordnance grade alloy frame that won't crack or allow the slide to come off. Other innovations include a three-position frame-mounted ambidextrous safety, which is more secure than a slide mounted safety, and allows for a classic SA "cocked-and-locked" mode, as well as functioning as a DA decocking lever. Available in fixed sight model 92 you'll be able to face any situation without compromise.

Features:

Loaded Chamber Indicator
Taurus provides a loaded chamber indicator on all new compact, medium and large frame pistols. As with all Taurus safety and security innovations, the indicator in no way interferes with the operation of your pistol and is provided at no extra cost, but gives you an "at-a-glance" verification that there is a round in the chamber. When a round is in the chamber, the ejector pops out of the slide, exposing a red strip just behind the ejection port. While any loaded chamber indicator is no substitute for common sense and safe firearm handling, it is one more example of Taurus' commitment to outstanding firearms.

3 Position Safety Decocker
Try the ambidextrous Three-Position Safety on any Taurus pistol capable of firing in both single action and double action. It's easily operated and provided at no additional charge. Depress with your thumb and safely drop the hammer to de-cock the pistol. The safety returns to the OFF position, ready for double action shooting. Push the safety up and your cocked pistol is safe to carry in the single action mode. When applied to a de-cocked pistol, safety is ON and the first shot is double action.

Taurus Security System (TSS)a
All the Taurus family of revolvers features the Taurus Security System, which provides instant-ready defense with built-in ability to secure your firearm and make it inoperable at the turn of a key. When the Security System is engaged, the pistol cannot be fired or cocked and the gun's manual safety cannot be disengaged. As with our revolver Security System, the device is part of the firearm and cannot be lost, and the same special Security Key works for both the revolver and pistol Systems (two keys come with each gun). To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun.
